experiments_run.name: Diverse Solution Generation
experiments_run.notes: Generated 10 valid solutions per N. Best generated solutions are 2x worse than baseline. Constructive heuristics cannot match the baseline's quality.

conclusion: Generating diverse solutions from scratch using constructive heuristics (spiral, hexagonal, bottom-left) produces solutions that are 2x worse than the baseline. The baseline was created by sophisticated C++ optimization with millions of iterations. Without access to similar optimization power or external data sources that found different local optima, we cannot improve on the baseline.
